## {{ rule.title }}

[26 U.S.C. § 901](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section901&num=0&edition=prelim) allows a credit for foreign income tax paid or accrued; [§ 905](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section905&num=0&edition=prelim) sets the timing rules (paid vs. accrued basis). Foreign tax that exceeded the [§ 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) limit in prior years rolls forward and is "available" alongside current-year payments. This stage assembles the per-basket pool of foreign tax that's eligible for crediting against U.S. tax.

{% set avail = rule.outputs[0].value | from_json -%}
For 2025:

- Current-year general-basket foreign tax (e.g., German wage tax allocated by IRS [Pub. 514](https://www.irs.gov/publications/p514) wage-share rules): **{{ avail.current_year_general_foreign_tax_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Current-year passive-basket foreign tax (e.g., German tax on dividends): **{{ avail.current_year_passive_foreign_tax_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- General-basket carryover from 2024 (excess from prior years per § 904(c)): **{{ avail.general_ftc_carryover_2024_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Passive-basket carryover from 2024: **{{ avail.passive_ftc_carryover_2024_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**

The available pool per basket is current-year + carryover. US25-14 will then take the lesser of available foreign tax and the per-basket [§ 904](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section904&num=0&edition=prelim) limit from US25-12.

